---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Kairong" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="page-shell space-y-6">
			<section class="surface-panel p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10">
				<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
				<div class="mt-3 space-y-4">
					<h1 class="section-heading max-w-3xl">
						A technical notebook for systems, tools, and research work.
					</h1>
					<p class="section-subtitle max-w-3xl">
						Hi, I'm Kairong. This blog is where I keep the durable version of what I learn while
						working on distributed systems, programming, engineering workflows, and academic writing.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section class="surface-panel mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-8 sm:px-10 sm:py-10">
				<div class="prose-content">
					<p>
						I use this space as a long-term archive rather than a stream of short updates. When a note
						ends up here, it is usually because I expect it to stay useful: a setup record, a design
						pattern, a writing rule, a debugging trail, or a small piece of engineering taste that is
						easy to forget.
					</p>
					<p>
						Most posts are practical. They try to make technical work feel calmer, clearer, and more
						repeatable.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
